lead_paragraph: Two Democratic women enjoy sizable leads over their Republican opponents in campaigns for California's two open Senate seats, according to a Field Poll released today. Both former Mayor Dianne Feinstein of San Francisco and Representative Barbara Boxer had 18-point leads.

headline.main: THE 1992 CAMPAIGN: On the Trail; WOMEN LEAD IN CALIFORNIA SENATE RACES
